review:
[Update] I've finished it now. Got 3 endings out of 6. It's pretty good from my first play. 

What can I say more? It is the best horror visual novel I've ever played. A work of art in itself. I'm planning to obtain each and every last achievement within the game. 

Like I said in the beginning, the game offers a varied palette of different characters, journalistic diary entries, insight into characters' lives and backgrounds, decisions to make that would save or threaten their lives, the fighting mechanics for each individual character. Although, I didn't get a big boss fight at the end. Must have needed the right choices. And I will remember that elevator scene! That was evil! Yangyang and Toefilo, that elevator scene was evil! 

These fighting mechanics might appear simple in nature, but they demand quick response, quick actions. Something I'm not good at. I thank the developer that did not hinder me from saving while having to make a decision. In some games like this, they don't let you save the moment and you have to replay the game all over again to get to that very moment. For this, I bow down to the dev or team that said "The save function remains!" 

PROS:
- Game warns beforehand of its strong contents;
- The story is excellently written;
- Beautiful scenery and images;
- Music fits every scene, atmosphere and feelings; 
- Wonderful voice-acting with accent;
- Memorable characters with real-life backgrounds;
- Jumpscares and scary fighting scenes are a few;
- Multiple endings;
- Saving and Loading possible whenever;
- Relationship, Branching Tree and lots of Extras.

NEUTER:
- Game contains display of foods and desserts. I'm not saying it's bad, but I carved for those while playing. Now I have a bag of chips with me. If you see me playing the game again, do know I have a bag of chips or biscuits with me. 

CONS:
- At some point in the pub, Ashton and Isabella are talking. When Ashton has to assure her, the audio that plays is not matching the subtitles and it says in a loud voice that Zach is dead. It also tends to repeat itself unnecessarily. I hope the devs hear about this and fix the problem. 
- Other things... I don't think so. No.

That's it. This game... Like I said. A piece of art. I've bought this game on discount a long time ago. Probably years and it was sitting on my library shelf. I thought to myself that it is time to be brave. I saw the screenshots and I was afraid to even touch it. But one of my New Year resolutions is to have courage! So, here I am! Both trembling and thrilled of the experience I went through these past nights. Every night from 6 p.m. to the middle of the night, I was there with my friends, the characters, and fought this maddening woman. I still got to discover the real story behind all these happenings, but you know what? I'm not scared anymore. Okay. Just a bit. But as much as I am scared, I want to play, to discover, to finally unearth the long lost secret of Ermegarden Mansion. (Hope I got the name right this time.)

Another brilliant terrifying experience from YangYang Mobile. What can I say? I'm at a lost of words. I must admit, when I saw that Saint Maker was out, I immediately purchased it and played it for five hour straight! 

PROS:
- Eerie atmosphere;
- Serenely quite music and good environment sounds;
- Incredible voice-acting;
- Intriguing story;
- Save and load points whenever needed;
- Few jumpscares;
- Extras!

CONS:
- Disclaimer missing (the story tackles with sensitive issues, like religion, sanctity and family matters);
- Not enough saving slots for the whole decision moments;
- The concept of Cornelia... uhm... (let's leave it like that);
- Not so complex branched as The Letter.

Although it might not be as excellent as The Letter, I think you should give it a try. It's a horror visual novel tackling sensitive issues. So be prepared for everything. Including your own dreams.
